    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-09T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-09T04:00:00-05:00" n="435"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/225: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-09T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 9—1:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>165. Following summary of telegrams sent to Tientsin.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“July 8, 5 p.m. Probability of military operations between Tuan and Tsao Kun
                        extremely serious. Warn Americans residing in <pb facs="0536" n="438"
                            xml:id="pg_438"/> Paotingfu that attack on city by armed forces
                        improbable [<hi rend="italic">is probable?</hi>] and for them to be ready to
                        leave at a moments notice, it is preferable for the women and children to
                        leave now.”</p>
                    <p>“July 8, 10 a.m. Attack on Paotingfu from Peking and Maliang from Tsinanfu
                        now in preparation. Advise Americans Paotingfu desirable to leave.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
